 Location
 New York, NY
 Open Date
 Aug 16, 2021
 Description
 The postdoc will work in the ML2 lab at NYU with Prof. He He and Prof. Kyunghyun Cho in the area of machine learning and natural language processing. 
 The research focus of this position includes, but is not limited to, learning from instructions, multimodal reasoning, few-shot learning, natural language generation, and QA/dialogue. 
 The postdoc will be encouraged to contribute to establishing research agenda, advise graduate and undergraduate students in the lab, and collaborate with other AI faculty at NYU. 
 Expected duration: 2 years with an option to renew one more year 
 Proposed start date: 11/1/2021 
 
 
 Qualifications 
 PhD in computer science or related disciplines 
 Strong publication record in NLP, ML, or related areas 
 Strong programming skills, including deep learning libraries such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, etc. 
 Strong communication and leadership skills 
 
 
 Application Instructions
